div
	h1 Database of Shockwave Properties for Various Materials
	p.
		You can view shock properties for various materials below. We'll make this searchable at some point. For now, use the list box 
		to select the material for which you want to view shockwave data. All data is excerpted from tables created by Thomas Ahrens, PhD.
		Table names and links are listed below.
	
	div
		h3 Available Materials
		select(class='mat' 
			ng-model='SelectedMaterial'
			ng-options='mat.Name + " (" + mat.Density + ")" for mat in materials')
	
	div
		ul
			li
				label #[b Name:] {{SelectedMaterial.Name}}
			li
				label #[b Formula:] {{SelectedMaterial.Formula}}
			
			li
				label #[b Density:] {{SelectedMaterial.Density}} Mg/m³
			
			li
				label #[b Special Measurement Conditions:] {{GetMeasurementCondition(SelectedMaterial.SpecialMeasurementIdentifier)}}
			
			li
				label #[b Internal References:] {{SelectedMaterial.References}}
			
			li
				label #[b Remarks:] {{SelectedMaterial.Remarks}}

	div
		h4 Phases List:
		table
			thead
				tr
					th Phase Number
					th Phase Type
					th C₀
					th Δ C₀ (error)
					th S
					th ΔS (error)
					th U (lower)
					th U (upper)
					th No. of Data
			tbody
				tr(ng-repeat='phase in SelectedMaterial.Phases')
					td {{phase.PhaseNumber}}
					td {{GetPhaseType(phase.PhaseNumber)}}
					td {{phase.IsentropicBulkSoundSpeed}}
					td {{phase.IsentropicBulkSoundSpeedError}}
					td {{phase.DimensionlessSparameter}}
					td {{phase.DimensionlessSparameterError}}
					td {{phase.ShockVelocityLower}}
					td {{phase.ShockVelocityUpper}}
					td {{phase.NumberOfData}}

	div
		h1 References List
		p.
